## Why This Is Asked
To gauge practical reasoning about logic constraints, Horn-SAT familiarity, and ability to reason about linear-time algorithms and incremental updates in data pipelines.

## Key Concepts
- Horn clauses
- Forward chaining
- Partial vs full assignments
- Complexity O(n+m)
- Cycle handling and inconsistency detection

## Code Example
```javascript
function solveHorn(rules, facts){
  const trueSet = new Set(facts);
  let queue = rules.filter(r => r.antecedent.every(v => trueSet.has(v)));
  while (queue.length){
    const r = queue.shift();
    if (!trueSet.has(r.consequent)){
      trueSet.add(r.consequent);
      queue = rules.filter(x => x.antecedent.every(v => trueSet.has(v)) && !trueSet.has(x.consequent));
    }
  }
  return trueSet;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you extend to non-Horn clauses?
- How would you handle incremental updates when facts change?
